<h2>TLDR</h2>

<p>
  We (sudo !!) collect the bare minimum data required to make the site work.
  We don't use anything we don't have to, and we delete as much as we can
  of it when we're done using it.
</p>

<p>
  One of the benefits of collecting next to nothing is that we can't screw something
  up that ends up affecting the end user.
</p>

<h2>Some informal definitions of legal terms</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Personal data</strong>: information that has the possibility
    of identifying you in itself or with other data. Examples are the username (handle)
    and password, which currently is all we track. Personal data is 
    defined in the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and we try to collect
    as little of this information as possible.
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Technical data</strong>: data that comes from a technical source, usually
    stemming in some way from your browser. Technical data can snowball into personal
    data because it can result in someone discovering Personal data. We also try to
    collect as little of this information as possible, because it can result in the
    above being derived from it.
  </li>
</ul>

