<h3>For writers</h3>

<h4>What's collected?</h4>

<p>
  The exact some stuff above, except also a username and password. This has a
  possibility of revealing personal information, which is why we safeguard it closely.
</p>

<h4>Why is it collected?</h4>

<p>
  Site functionality, compliance with the law when applicable, and troubleshooting
  when applicable. We feel morally obligated to not take the same path as many
  other companies have, like Google or Facebook, in taking user data and brokering
  it out.
</p>

<h3>Cookie usage</h3>

<p>
  As mentioned above, cookies are only in place because they are a necessary
  authentication method. If you're someone writing for the site, you have to
  enable cookies in order to write, because otherwise we can't be sure who is
  the author of any given article.
</p>

<p>
  However, if you're just a reader, cookies are not required but the site
  will ask your browser for them anyways because it can't tell the difference
  between a logged in user and a non-logged in user until after visiting the site.
  You can disable cookies if you want and it will have no impact on the site.
</p>

<h3>Locking down your data</h3>

<p>
  Sudo !! follows industry best-practices and, whenever possible, tries to
  <i>not</i> collect information because it's in both our best interest, and
  for every user on the site to never have anything bad happen to their
  information.  
</p>

<p>
  In the event of any breach that touches Personal Information, we will act
  promptly to mitigate the breach and notify all affected users ASAP.
</p>

<p>
  All forms of communication take place over HTTPS using the latest TLS version.
  When sensitive data is stored, it's encrypted using industry standards. We also
  enforce things like passwords to be strong to make bruteforce attacks more difficult.
</p>

<p>
  It should go without saying that no transit protocol or storage method is 100% secure.
</p>

